<para id="fs-idm37086800">A student goes to the library. Let events <emphasis effect="italics">B</emphasis> = the student checks out a book and <emphasis effect="italics">D</emphasis> = the student checks out a DVD. Suppose that <emphasis effect="italics">P</emphasis>(<emphasis effect="italics">B</emphasis>) = .40, <emphasis effect="italics">P</emphasis>(<emphasis effect="italics">D</emphasis>) = .30, and <emphasis effect="italics">P</emphasis>(<emphasis effect="italics">D</emphasis>|<emphasis effect="italics">B</emphasis>) = .5.</para><list id="fs-idm40366288" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item>Find <emphasis effect="italics">P</emphasis>(<emphasis effect="italics">B′</emphasis>).</item>
